WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.423 --> 00:00:08.758
[intriguing. electronic music playing]

2
00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:14.973
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

3
00:00:16.016 --> 00:00:19.394
[marker sliding on paper]

4
00:00:50.592 --> 00:00:51.468
[sighs]

5
00:00:55.013 --> 00:00:57.057
-Lee Min-yeong.
-[girl 1] Here.

6
00:00:58.016 --> 00:00:59.517
Jang Han-seul.

7
00:01:00.685 --> 00:01:01.644
Jang Han-seul?

8
00:01:02.520 --> 00:01:03.813
Jang Han-seul?

9
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:05.899
[student coughs]

10
00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:09.444
-Heo Do-jun.
-[boy 1] Here.

11
00:01:11.780 --> 00:01:12.781
[sighs]

12
00:01:13.698 --> 00:01:16.326
I finished marking the assignments
you submitted last week.

13
00:01:16.409 --> 00:01:19.454
They're right over there.
You can come and get them after class.

14
00:01:19.537 --> 00:01:20.497
[girl 1] Yes. Professor.

15
00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:21.581
[indistinct chatter]

16
00:01:21.664 --> 00:01:22.957
[girl 2] Did you take notes?

17
00:01:24.375 --> 00:01:27.128
-Is it okay if I look at them?
-[girl 3] Sure. I'll send them to you.

18
00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:30.381
[girl 2] Hey. did you understand
what he was talking about today? I've…

19
00:01:30.465 --> 00:01:31.591
[indistinct chatter]

20
00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:33.593
[girl 4] Professor.

21
00:01:33.676 --> 00:01:34.886
Professor!

22
00:01:37.639 --> 00:01:39.307
Um. what's…

23
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:41.684
I mean. "trash"?

24
00:01:41.768 --> 00:01:43.853
Are you calling my paper trash?

25
00:01:44.437 --> 00:01:45.772
Don't you know?

26
00:01:46.397 --> 00:01:48.316
I'm an influencer.

27
00:01:49.150 --> 00:01:51.736
Do you have any idea what that is?

28
00:01:52.695 --> 00:01:56.407
It means I have over 30.000 subscribers
on my blog alone.

29
00:01:56.491 --> 00:01:58.701
Do you know how many likes
I get every day?

30
00:01:58.785 --> 00:01:59.786
Really?

31
00:02:00.495 --> 00:02:02.080
That's fascinating.

32
00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:04.374
What's it called? "The Trash Can"?

33
00:02:04.457 --> 00:02:06.751
Although. if it's full
of writing like this.

34
00:02:06.835 --> 00:02:09.295
I think you should call it
"The Dump." instead.

35
00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:14.300
Ah… 12 paragraphs.

36
00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:17.428
167 sentences.

37
00:02:17.512 --> 00:02:20.974
Maybe you think this is a piece of writing
because you filled some pages with words.

38
00:02:21.057 --> 00:02:24.686
Unfortunately. none of the sentences
in here mean anything at all.

39
00:02:25.186 --> 00:02:28.565
That's because nothing in here
is personal and heartfelt.

40
00:02:29.357 --> 00:02:32.402
The whole thing's a series
of cheap clichés and sentimentality.

41
00:02:32.485 --> 00:02:35.822
not to mention what you copied
from other people's work.

42
00:02:36.614 --> 00:02:38.449
What term should I use
for this stream of words

43
00:02:38.533 --> 00:02:41.911
you've vomited out
without even understanding it yourself?

44
00:02:42.412 --> 00:02:45.665
So if you think there's a better word
for this than "trash." tell me.

45
00:02:48.209 --> 00:02:50.795
I'd be happy to use that word instead.

46
00:02:50.879 --> 00:02:52.380
[dissonant. tense music playing]

47
00:02:52.463 --> 00:02:53.673
[paper rustles brusquely]

48
00:02:56.801 --> 00:02:58.761
-[huffs]
-Can I go now?

49
00:03:00.054 --> 00:03:02.056
[rhythmic acoustic music playing]

50
00:03:03.266 --> 00:03:05.685
[boy 2] That crazy bastard. Ignore him.

51
00:03:05.768 --> 00:03:07.687
[girl 5] Want me to kill him for you?

52
00:03:07.770 --> 00:03:09.147
Ugh! He's the worst.

53
00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:10.857
[boy 2] If this weren't a required course…

54
00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:11.774
[girl 5 scoffs]

55
00:03:11.858 --> 00:03:12.775
[boy 2] …I'd drop it.

56
00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:15.236
[boy 3] I heard Heo Mun-oh does that
because he can't write.

57
00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:16.279
[girl 5] Huh?

58
00:03:17.155 --> 00:03:19.657
[boy 3] <i>Some seniors told me all about it.</i>

59
00:03:20.158 --> 00:03:24.287
<i>He's only ever written one novel.</i>
<i>and that was. like. 20 years ago.</i>

60
00:03:24.787 --> 00:03:27.957
<i>And ever since. he hasn't been able</i>
<i>to write anything else.</i>

61
00:03:28.458 --> 00:03:31.502
<i>He wants to. but he can't.</i>
<i>no matter how hard he fucking tries.</i>

62
00:03:31.586 --> 00:03:35.590
<i>So he takes all his frustration</i>
<i>and self-loathing out on his students.</i>

63
00:03:36.299 --> 00:03:37.467
<i>What a loser.</i>

64
00:03:37.967 --> 00:03:39.510
RESEARCH IN PROGRESS
DO NOT DISTURB

65
00:03:40.678 --> 00:03:42.347
Oh. Mun-oh. there you are.

66
00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:45.016
[chuckles] Your door was open. so…

67
00:03:45.683 --> 00:03:46.851
[music fades]

68
00:03:48.311 --> 00:03:50.939
Hello again. Mr. Park. Back so soon?

69
00:03:51.022 --> 00:03:52.899
Oh. yeah. I guess so.

70
00:03:52.982 --> 00:03:54.525
Well. I missed you. Mun-oh.

71
00:03:54.609 --> 00:03:57.654
Hey. not again. I told you
I'd rather we keep it professional.

72
00:03:57.737 --> 00:03:58.947
Yes. Mr. Heo.

73
00:03:59.030 --> 00:04:00.114
[chuckles]

74
00:04:00.198 --> 00:04:02.242
Ah. that just sounds so formal.

75
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:03.576
[chuckles]

76
00:04:03.660 --> 00:04:05.411
So you got home all right yesterday?

77
00:04:05.495 --> 00:04:08.373
-[Mun-oh] Coffee?
-Oh. no. thanks. I just had one.

78
00:04:09.165 --> 00:04:11.334
Hey. what's this? Oh. my goodness!

79
00:04:11.417 --> 00:04:12.919
You're so stubborn. Mun-oh.

80
00:04:13.002 --> 00:04:15.380
You're still taking attendance
on paper. huh?

81
00:04:15.463 --> 00:04:18.466
-[Mun-oh sighs]
-Look. I'll install the program for you.

82
00:04:18.549 --> 00:04:21.261
-It's way more convenient.
-Oh. no. thank you.

83
00:04:21.344 --> 00:04:23.304
I like my way just fine.

84
00:04:23.846 --> 00:04:25.431
So what brings you here?

85
00:04:25.515 --> 00:04:27.392
You wouldn't come
from the College of Engineering

86
00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:28.309
without a reason.

87
00:04:28.393 --> 00:04:30.019
Oh. uh… [chuckles]

88
00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:32.313
I actually wanted
to bring this up yesterday but forgot.

89
00:04:32.397 --> 00:04:34.148
-[Mun-oh] Mm-hmm.
-Listen. Mun-oh.

90
00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:37.944
I understand you know
Kim Su-hun. the author.

91
00:04:41.614 --> 00:04:43.866
Who? Uh. Kim Su-hun?

92
00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:44.909
Yeah. yeah.

93
00:04:45.451 --> 00:04:47.078
You went to university together.

94
00:04:47.161 --> 00:04:50.623
Man. I had no idea
you were so well-connected. Mun-oh.

95
00:04:50.707 --> 00:04:52.166
I wish I'd known it earlier.

96
00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:54.877
I would have asked for your help
getting him here years ago.

97
00:04:54.961 --> 00:04:56.254
What do you mean?

98
00:04:56.337 --> 00:04:58.881
Uh… I think I told you about this.

99
00:04:58.965 --> 00:05:00.008
Um…

100
00:05:00.091 --> 00:05:04.512
I organize monthly cultural events
for the College of Engineering. Hmm?

101
00:05:04.595 --> 00:05:07.557
Our students don't get out much.
so I volunteered to--

102
00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:08.766
Just get to the point.

103
00:05:08.850 --> 00:05:11.269
Ah. yes! To the point. [chuckles]

104
00:05:11.352 --> 00:05:15.273
The point is. we hope that
Kim Su-hun will be our guest next month.

105
00:05:15.356 --> 00:05:19.610
Uh. to give a lecture on his new novel.
followed by a conversation.

106
00:05:19.694 --> 00:05:23.323
And I hope you will host
that conversation.

107
00:05:25.283 --> 00:05:26.576
[Mun-oh sighs softly]

108
00:05:26.659 --> 00:05:27.535
[Mr. Park] Hmm?

109
00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:32.457
-Host the conversation?
-Yes.

110
00:05:32.957 --> 00:05:35.543
It was Mr. Kim who first suggested it.

111
00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.258
Kim Su-hun suggested it?

112
00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:45.094
-Yeah.
-And what did he say?

113
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:48.056
Well. he said he thought
it would be more comfortable and fun

114
00:05:48.139 --> 00:05:49.682
if a friend hosted it.

115
00:05:49.766 --> 00:05:51.434
He said he'd come if you did it.

116
00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:55.146
[sighs softly]

117
00:05:55.229 --> 00:05:56.856
[brooding string music playing]

118
00:05:57.607 --> 00:05:59.150
Kim Su-hun said that?

119
00:06:00.276 --> 00:06:01.194
[Mr. Park] Yeah.

120
00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:07.533
-[music continues]
-[car horns honking]

121
00:06:07.617 --> 00:06:09.118
[man 1] Careful. Mr. Gu. It's slippery.

122
00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:12.163
-[man 2] Gonna write a good article?
-Oh. yeah. absolutely.

123
00:06:12.246 --> 00:06:14.582
Just make sure you're ready
to print more copies of the book.

124
00:06:14.665 --> 00:06:16.334
-[Mun-oh] Su-hun.
-[men chuckle]

125
00:06:16.417 --> 00:06:17.293
Oh.

126
00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:21.714
-[man 1] It's just up here.
-Oh. Mun-oh. Just a second.

127
00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:23.925
-Uh. Mr. Gu?
-[Mr. Gu] Hmm?

128
00:06:24.008 --> 00:06:26.427
[Su-hun] Please. go on ahead.
I'll be right there.

129
00:06:26.511 --> 00:06:27.387
[man 2] Okay. sure.

130
00:06:27.470 --> 00:06:30.139
[man 1] Don't take too long.
The real interview starts now. you know.

131
00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:32.433
-[Su-hun] Right.
-[man 2] We'll be at the pork restaurant.

132
00:06:32.517 --> 00:06:33.935
-See you there.
-See you there.

133
00:06:34.018 --> 00:06:35.561
[distant police siren wailing]

134
00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:38.981
I should have given you a call earlier.

135
00:06:39.065 --> 00:06:40.441
I'm sorry about that.

136
00:06:40.525 --> 00:06:41.442
Yeah.

137
00:06:41.526 --> 00:06:44.153
Weren't we supposed
to have dinner together tonight?

138
00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:46.531
Um. that's what I thought. anyway.

139
00:06:46.614 --> 00:06:48.825
Yeah. for sure. That was the plan.

140
00:06:49.409 --> 00:06:50.952
We need to talk. actually.

141
00:06:51.035 --> 00:06:54.080
Then. this afternoon.
Mr. Gu came to see us unexpectedly.

142
00:06:54.580 --> 00:06:55.665
You know who he is. right?

143
00:06:55.748 --> 00:06:58.751
Yeah. sure. Of course. I do.
Who doesn't know Gu Yeong-ho?

144
00:06:58.835 --> 00:07:01.003
I've never seen him in person
before. though. [chuckles]

145
00:07:02.713 --> 00:07:03.589
Listen.

146
00:07:04.674 --> 00:07:06.050
you wanted to talk?

147
00:07:06.551 --> 00:07:07.844
What about?

148
00:07:09.720 --> 00:07:13.015
If it's the favor I asked you.

149
00:07:13.724 --> 00:07:14.559
did you decide?

150
00:07:16.686 --> 00:07:17.645
Yeah.

151
00:07:20.481 --> 00:07:23.067
Sorry. I can't write you a testimonial.

152
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:26.320
I feel like I've been writing
too many testimonials lately.

153
00:07:28.781 --> 00:07:30.908
Oh. too… too many?

154
00:07:30.992 --> 00:07:32.368
[somber music playing]

155
00:07:32.452 --> 00:07:33.536
But you…

156
00:07:34.412 --> 00:07:35.371
you did read it?

157
00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:36.873
Of course. I did.

158
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:39.208
Let's talk later.

159
00:07:39.709 --> 00:07:41.794
-Soon though. all right?
-Wait. Su-hun.

160
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:45.256
Tell me. What is it? What did you think?

161
00:07:45.756 --> 00:07:47.258
Tell me now. please.

162
00:07:49.552 --> 00:07:50.720
[sighs]

163
00:07:50.803 --> 00:07:51.929
[wind howls]

164
00:07:58.019 --> 00:07:58.936
[lighter clicks]

165
00:08:03.774 --> 00:08:04.775
[music ends]

166
00:08:06.527 --> 00:08:07.737
[grunts]

167
00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:19.373
[object clatters]

168
00:08:44.774 --> 00:08:46.484
[acoustic guitar strums softly]

169
00:08:49.737 --> 00:08:53.783
I had trouble understanding
what the writer was attempting to say.

170
00:08:53.866 --> 00:08:54.867
[inhales sharply]

171
00:08:54.951 --> 00:08:56.285
Honestly. I thought.

172
00:08:57.078 --> 00:08:59.830
why would you bother writing
without saying anything?

173
00:08:59.914 --> 00:09:01.207
[guitar music continues]

174
00:09:01.707 --> 00:09:03.834
There's nothing wrong with that. you know?

175
00:09:05.461 --> 00:09:07.630
But most of all. you should

176
00:09:08.506 --> 00:09:10.550
revisit how to write good sentences.

177
00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:12.510
[music continues]

178
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:27.733
[Mun-oh] <i>That's why</i>
<i>the first sentence is so important.</i>

179
00:09:27.817 --> 00:09:28.734
[music ends]

180
00:09:29.443 --> 00:09:30.736
[sighs]

181
00:09:31.821 --> 00:09:35.950
It's because once the author
writes the first sentence.

182
00:09:36.033 --> 00:09:38.744
they've taken their first step
into the story.

183
00:09:41.872 --> 00:09:43.749
For example. listen to this.

184
00:09:45.501 --> 00:09:47.670
"How glad I am that I am gone."

185
00:09:48.170 --> 00:09:50.590
"Dear friend. what a thing
is the human heart."

186
00:09:52.633 --> 00:09:53.593
"To leave you.

187
00:09:55.428 --> 00:09:58.014
whom I love so dearly. and yet feel glad."

188
00:09:59.056 --> 00:10:01.267
Can anyone tell me
which novel that's from?

189
00:10:05.521 --> 00:10:06.564
You don't know?

190
00:10:12.111 --> 00:10:14.405
A classic among classics.

191
00:10:14.488 --> 00:10:16.532
-Goethe's--
-[music plays on cell phone]

192
00:10:16.616 --> 00:10:17.450
[music stops]

193
00:10:17.533 --> 00:10:18.659
[student giggles]

194
00:10:19.577 --> 00:10:20.578
Who was that?

195
00:10:22.705 --> 00:10:23.873
Whose phone was that?

196
00:10:27.293 --> 00:10:28.336
I'm sorry.

197
00:10:28.419 --> 00:10:30.171
[students snickering softly]

198
00:10:30.254 --> 00:10:31.672
[indistinct whispering]

199
00:10:34.550 --> 00:10:39.221
[sighs] The first sentence
of <i>The Sorrows of Young Werther </i>by Goethe.

200
00:10:40.056 --> 00:10:43.142
As I'm sure you all know.

201
00:10:43.225 --> 00:10:46.145
it's written in the form of letters
that Werther sends to his friend Albert.

202
00:10:46.228 --> 00:10:47.980
Do you think my class is a joke?

203
00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:54.028
Do you think I'm a joke? Huh?

204
00:10:56.530 --> 00:10:57.615
Stand up.

205
00:10:58.532 --> 00:10:59.742
Right now.

206
00:11:01.577 --> 00:11:02.745
You're not going to?

207
00:11:03.996 --> 00:11:05.164
Then get out!

208
00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:08.918
Go on. get outta here!

209
00:11:09.001 --> 00:11:11.837
[boy 1] It's not Albert. It's Wilhelm.

210
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:14.632
[indistinct whispers]

211
00:11:16.133 --> 00:11:17.301
What did you say?

212
00:11:18.260 --> 00:11:20.262
[boy 1] Werther's friend is named Wilhelm.

213
00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:26.268
Albert is the… fiancé of Lotte.
the woman Werther loves.

214
00:11:28.979 --> 00:11:29.855
[chuckles softly]

215
00:11:30.815 --> 00:11:32.692
Albert is Werther's rival.

216
00:11:33.567 --> 00:11:36.737
The one he's jealous of but also idolizes.

217
00:11:37.405 --> 00:11:38.989
[chuckles] Maybe

218
00:11:40.533 --> 00:11:43.411
in the sense
that all of those things are a part of it…

219
00:11:43.911 --> 00:11:45.037
[chuckles]

220
00:11:45.121 --> 00:11:47.248
…you could say they're actually friends.

221
00:11:48.708 --> 00:11:50.292
The object of his envy

222
00:11:51.919 --> 00:11:53.295
is also his friend.

223
00:11:53.379 --> 00:11:55.381
[students jeeringly] Ooh…

224
00:11:55.464 --> 00:11:57.174
[scattered snickers]

225
00:11:57.258 --> 00:11:58.801
[brooding music playing]

226
00:11:58.884 --> 00:12:02.263
Professor… I think time's up now.

227
00:12:05.266 --> 00:12:06.183
[Mun-oh sighs]

228
00:12:07.935 --> 00:12:09.228
That's it for today.

229
00:12:10.187 --> 00:12:12.189
[objects shuffling]

230
00:12:14.775 --> 00:12:16.068
[boy 2] Hey. get up.

231
00:12:16.152 --> 00:12:17.611
[brooding music continues]

232
00:12:33.043 --> 00:12:35.296
FUNDAMENTALS OF WRITING
CONCEPTS AND PRACTICES

233
00:12:35.379 --> 00:12:36.338
PROFESSOR HEO MUN-OH

234
00:12:36.422 --> 00:12:37.923
ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING
LEE KANG

235
00:12:38.007 --> 00:12:39.925
-Hey. thanks!
-[gentle piano music playing]

236
00:12:40.009 --> 00:12:42.136
If it weren't for you. I'd be in trouble.

237
00:12:42.887 --> 00:12:45.097
So how about I take you out for lunch?

238
00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:49.018
Whatever you want.
Anything. Fried chicken. pizza…

239
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:53.230
[Kang] <i>But if jealousy came</i>
<i>before affection.</i>

240
00:12:53.856 --> 00:12:56.901
<i>could that really be called a friendship?</i>

241
00:12:56.984 --> 00:12:58.194
[piano music continues]

242
00:13:00.529 --> 00:13:03.949
<i>I first met Se-yun in the winter</i>
<i>before we started school.</i>

243
00:13:04.033 --> 00:13:06.494
<i>It was… a coincidence.</i>

244
00:13:14.001 --> 00:13:16.212
Hey. what are you doing? Clear the table.

245
00:13:16.712 --> 00:13:17.755
[tuts]

246
00:13:17.838 --> 00:13:19.256
Hey. is this. uh…

247
00:13:24.762 --> 00:13:25.763
[music fades]

248
00:13:32.436 --> 00:13:33.813
Are you looking for this?

249
00:13:34.313 --> 00:13:36.190
Hey. thank you. Thanks a lot.

250
00:13:37.733 --> 00:13:39.193
It's okay! I found it!

251
00:13:41.612 --> 00:13:43.614
[quirky. melodic music playing]

252
00:13:48.410 --> 00:13:49.995
[no audible dialogue]

253
00:13:55.918 --> 00:13:57.545
[students cheering]

254
00:13:57.628 --> 00:13:59.713
[Se-yun] Okay. great. Thanks so much.

255
00:13:59.797 --> 00:14:00.673
Thanks.

256
00:14:01.799 --> 00:14:05.594
[Kang] <i>Our meeting was a coincidence.</i>
<i>but becoming friends</i>

257
00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:07.930
<i>wasn't.</i>

258
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:10.182
<i>It was my plan.</i>

259
00:14:10.266 --> 00:14:11.392
CODING CLUB

260
00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:15.271
[Se-yun sighs]

261
00:14:15.980 --> 00:14:17.106
[music fades]

262
00:14:17.189 --> 00:14:18.357
[rummaging]

263
00:14:18.440 --> 00:14:19.316
Oh.

264
00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:20.818
You're in YDOC too?

265
00:14:21.485 --> 00:14:22.653
I've got the same bag.

266
00:14:25.739 --> 00:14:28.742
I'm Kim Se-yun. I just started
in Library Science. And you?

267
00:14:29.243 --> 00:14:30.411
Hi. I'm Lee Kang.

268
00:14:30.494 --> 00:14:32.496
-Electronic Engineering.
-Whoa!

269
00:14:32.997 --> 00:14:34.790
You're in engineering
<i>and </i>taking this class?

270
00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:37.001
Well. actually. it is a general course.

271
00:14:40.796 --> 00:14:42.548
Hey. do you know how to code already?

272
00:14:43.048 --> 00:14:45.926
'Cause I don't know anything yet.
I just joined because I like gaming.

273
00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:47.219
[indistinct chatter]

274
00:14:49.972 --> 00:14:51.891
-Coding isn't difficult.
-[door closes]

275
00:14:52.391 --> 00:14:53.267
It's easy.

276
00:14:54.268 --> 00:14:55.311
Really?

277
00:14:58.355 --> 00:15:00.316
Wow! How do you do this?

278
00:15:01.066 --> 00:15:02.067
Can you show me how?

279
00:15:02.776 --> 00:15:03.694
Not right now.

280
00:15:04.194 --> 00:15:05.571
I have to go to work soon.

281
00:15:07.489 --> 00:15:09.533
Tomorrow? At my house?

282
00:15:10.409 --> 00:15:12.161
[Kang] <i>My plan was a success.</i>

283
00:15:12.661 --> 00:15:13.954
-Your house?
-Mm-hmm.

284
00:15:14.038 --> 00:15:16.624
<i>-I finally became friends with Se-yun.</i>
-What's good for you?

285
00:15:16.707 --> 00:15:19.084
<i>Friends who could go</i>
<i>to each other's houses.</i>

286
00:15:19.168 --> 00:15:20.878
TO BE CONTINUED..

287
00:15:21.962 --> 00:15:23.130
[chuckles softly]

288
00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:38.520
[sighs deeply]

289
00:15:39.897 --> 00:15:41.607
[soft. whimsical music playing]

290
00:15:46.946 --> 00:15:47.988
[chuckles softly]

291
00:15:51.200 --> 00:15:52.242
[music continues]

292
00:16:06.173 --> 00:16:07.883
[paper rustling]

293
00:16:10.135 --> 00:16:12.054
[Kang] <i>Can you be nostalgic</i>

294
00:16:12.846 --> 00:16:14.807
<i>over a place you've never been?</i>

295
00:16:15.349 --> 00:16:16.308
[music lifts]

296
00:16:17.601 --> 00:16:19.812
<i>Can you be filled with longing</i>

297
00:16:20.521 --> 00:16:22.731
<i>for a person you've never met?</i>

298
00:16:27.319 --> 00:16:28.612
[music becomes uplifting]

299
00:16:30.322 --> 00:16:34.660
<i>It was my first time at Se-yun's house.</i>
<i>but it felt familiar.</i>

300
00:16:34.743 --> 00:16:37.413
<i>It looked exactly like it did</i>
<i>in the photos.</i>

301
00:16:39.498 --> 00:16:41.000
Come on in. This way.

302
00:16:43.544 --> 00:16:44.586
[music fades]

303
00:16:45.963 --> 00:16:46.797
Mom.

304
00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:52.344
-Ah. you're home.
-[Se-yun] This is my friend.

305
00:16:52.428 --> 00:16:55.014
-He's from the coding club.
-[quirky. melodic music playing]

306
00:16:55.097 --> 00:16:57.141
I told you he was coming over.

307
00:16:58.350 --> 00:17:00.019
Oh yeah. That's right.

308
00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:02.354
Hi. I'm Lee Kang.

309
00:17:02.855 --> 00:17:04.398
It's nice to meet you.

310
00:17:04.481 --> 00:17:05.607
[dreamy music playing]

311
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.901
<i>No. it was different from the photos.</i>

312
00:17:07.985 --> 00:17:11.447
<i>Everything was even more beautiful</i>
<i>than I'd expected. The house…</i>

313
00:17:11.530 --> 00:17:13.532
You're so good at this. Seriously.

314
00:17:13.615 --> 00:17:14.825
<i>…and the people.</i>

315
00:17:14.908 --> 00:17:17.661
-[Se-yun] Good job. huh?
-[mother chuckles] Yes. good job.

316
00:17:18.245 --> 00:17:19.830
-Of course.
-[Se-yun chuckles]

317
00:17:19.913 --> 00:17:22.249
-[dreamy music continues]
-[woman vocalizing]

318
00:17:29.006 --> 00:17:30.215
[music intensifies]

319
00:17:53.030 --> 00:17:54.448
[music peaks. then fades]

320
00:17:54.531 --> 00:17:56.492
[woman] "To be continued."

321
00:17:56.575 --> 00:17:59.495
Oh my. What is this? Who wrote it?

322
00:17:59.578 --> 00:18:00.829
Just. you know…

323
00:18:01.914 --> 00:18:03.123
What do you think?

324
00:18:04.208 --> 00:18:05.459
Not sure.

325
00:18:07.127 --> 00:18:10.047
So he wanted to be friends
with this other boy.

326
00:18:10.964 --> 00:18:12.341
No. that's not it.

327
00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:14.343
He acted like they were friends.

328
00:18:14.426 --> 00:18:16.386
because he wanted
to go to his house. right?

329
00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:19.181
Oh. I'm confused. What does he want?

330
00:18:19.264 --> 00:18:20.808
Why would he write this?

331
00:18:20.891 --> 00:18:22.559
Oh. for God's sake.

332
00:18:22.643 --> 00:18:25.729
I wanted an expert opinion
from you. not this.

333
00:18:25.813 --> 00:18:27.773
You're asking the same questions I did.

334
00:18:28.273 --> 00:18:31.193
What do you think the psychology
of this is. if you were to guess?

335
00:18:31.693 --> 00:18:34.321
[sighs] I can't tell just based on this.

336
00:18:36.949 --> 00:18:39.868
But it doesn't seem like
it's anything too complex.

337
00:18:39.952 --> 00:18:41.662
[smacks lips] He's envious.

338
00:18:42.579 --> 00:18:44.665
He must have seen something
he desperately wanted

339
00:18:44.748 --> 00:18:45.916
in that friend of his.

340
00:18:45.999 --> 00:18:48.752
And since he can't do anything
about that feeling.

341
00:18:48.836 --> 00:18:50.671
he's letting it out through writing.

342
00:18:53.632 --> 00:18:55.134
While it's a little odd.

343
00:18:55.634 --> 00:18:58.428
putting these feelings into writing
is a good thing.

344
00:18:59.805 --> 00:19:00.806
Hmm.

345
00:19:01.723 --> 00:19:03.475
I'm curious what happens next. though.

346
00:19:04.059 --> 00:19:05.602
He's a very good writer.

347
00:19:07.062 --> 00:19:10.440
I think… he's the best
writing student you've had.

348
00:19:11.900 --> 00:19:13.235
[clicks tongue. inhales]

349
00:19:13.318 --> 00:19:14.778
Yes. by far.

350
00:19:15.779 --> 00:19:17.823
Well? Are you gonna mentor him.
do you think?

351
00:19:18.323 --> 00:19:19.658
Don't be ridiculous.

352
00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:21.243
All right.

353
00:19:21.743 --> 00:19:22.995
Hey. by the way…

354
00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:29.126
when was the last time you came in here?

355
00:19:29.960 --> 00:19:30.961
Do you know?

356
00:19:34.089 --> 00:19:35.007
Good night.

357
00:19:39.011 --> 00:19:40.095
[footsteps depart]

358
00:19:40.179 --> 00:19:41.555
[door opens. closes]

359
00:19:41.638 --> 00:19:42.681
[chuckles softly]

360
00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:48.896
[grunts]

361
00:19:50.314 --> 00:19:52.024
[sighs deeply]

362
00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:54.401
[sniffs]

363
00:19:55.694 --> 00:19:57.529
[quirky instrumental music playing]

364
00:20:00.199 --> 00:20:02.284
[woman] <i>I'm curious</i>
<i>what happens next. though.</i>

365
00:20:03.493 --> 00:20:06.872
<i>I think… he's the best</i>
<i>writing student you've had.</i>

366
00:20:07.456 --> 00:20:09.833
<i>Well. are you gonna mentor him.</i>
<i>do you think?</i>

367
00:20:11.919 --> 00:20:13.086
[exhales pensively]

368
00:20:17.132 --> 00:20:18.342
[quirky music continues]

369
00:20:29.519 --> 00:20:30.729
[music builds]

370
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:33.565
[music peaks. then stops]

371
00:20:34.650 --> 00:20:36.485
You asked me to stay behind?

372
00:20:37.861 --> 00:20:41.657
Is there something
you wanted to… say to me?

373
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:46.703
You humiliated me
in front of the other students.

374
00:20:47.454 --> 00:20:48.664
Did you get a kick out of that?

375
00:20:50.374 --> 00:20:51.583
[chuckles] Oh.

376
00:20:51.667 --> 00:20:52.834
[cell phone vibrates]

377
00:20:53.877 --> 00:20:55.045
[rummages]

378
00:20:55.128 --> 00:20:56.004
[sighs]

379
00:21:02.219 --> 00:21:03.220
[inaudible]

380
00:21:04.263 --> 00:21:05.138
[Kang sighs]

381
00:21:05.722 --> 00:21:07.391
Is that Kim Se-yun?

382
00:21:09.977 --> 00:21:11.061
Yeah.

383
00:21:11.728 --> 00:21:14.231
Does he know what you're writing about?

384
00:21:14.731 --> 00:21:15.899
Has he read it?

385
00:21:17.150 --> 00:21:18.026
No.

386
00:21:18.860 --> 00:21:21.154
You're the only one who reads them. right?

387
00:21:22.072 --> 00:21:23.615
That's what you said the first class.

388
00:21:28.662 --> 00:21:29.705
Have a seat.

389
00:21:36.628 --> 00:21:37.629
[Kang grunts softly]

390
00:21:39.256 --> 00:21:40.382
[sighs]

391
00:21:42.718 --> 00:21:43.593
[smacks lips]

392
00:21:44.678 --> 00:21:46.596
[sighs deeply]

393
00:21:48.307 --> 00:21:49.266
Now.

394
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:53.145
What do you want to write about?

395
00:21:53.937 --> 00:21:55.188
What are you trying to say?

396
00:21:56.315 --> 00:21:57.149
I don't know.

397
00:21:57.649 --> 00:22:00.527
You said to just write
whatever we felt like.

398
00:22:01.028 --> 00:22:01.987
So that's what I did.

399
00:22:02.070 --> 00:22:04.156
[sighs] No. no.

400
00:22:06.616 --> 00:22:09.286
You understand what I'm asking you.

401
00:22:10.829 --> 00:22:12.164
You don't have to pretend.

402
00:22:20.547 --> 00:22:21.590
[inhales pensively]

403
00:22:22.090 --> 00:22:23.884
Uh. you…

404
00:22:26.970 --> 00:22:28.513
envy him. don't you?

405
00:22:30.057 --> 00:22:31.683
You wish you could be him.

406
00:22:33.518 --> 00:22:35.562
That's why you wrote this. isn't it?

407
00:22:36.313 --> 00:22:37.689
[tense music playing]

408
00:22:40.692 --> 00:22:41.777
You know what?

409
00:22:43.487 --> 00:22:47.783
There's nothing about you
in Kim Se-yun's assignment.

410
00:22:48.617 --> 00:22:52.954
It seems he doesn't care about you.
whether you envy him or not.

411
00:22:53.955 --> 00:22:55.957
You're the only one who's suffering.

412
00:22:56.041 --> 00:22:57.042
[Kang chuckles softly]

413
00:23:00.170 --> 00:23:01.713
Do you know. Professor?

414
00:23:03.673 --> 00:23:05.008
Have you felt it?

415
00:23:06.051 --> 00:23:07.427
[tense music rises]

416
00:23:12.140 --> 00:23:13.308
[music halts]

417
00:23:13.392 --> 00:23:14.267
Oh.

418
00:23:15.143 --> 00:23:19.773
So what you're saying is
that I should write about something else?

419
00:23:20.273 --> 00:23:22.567
[chuckles] There's nothing else
I wanna write about.

420
00:23:22.651 --> 00:23:25.070
No. no. write! Write about this.

421
00:23:25.153 --> 00:23:26.738
I wanted to say

422
00:23:27.280 --> 00:23:28.323
you should keep writing.

423
00:23:28.407 --> 00:23:30.158
Even if it's hard. write through it.

424
00:23:31.535 --> 00:23:34.287
It's so important to have something
you wanna write about.

425
00:23:37.749 --> 00:23:38.834
You're talented.

426
00:23:43.463 --> 00:23:44.714
If you want.

427
00:23:45.674 --> 00:23:48.468
I'm willing to offer you
individual lessons once a week.

428
00:23:49.177 --> 00:23:51.847
-Individual?
-Mm-hmm. That's right.

429
00:23:54.141 --> 00:23:57.686
I wanna offer you extra lessons.
more of my time. What? Don't you get it?

430
00:23:57.769 --> 00:23:59.104
No. I do. It's just…

431
00:24:00.856 --> 00:24:02.524
I have to work as well.

432
00:24:05.026 --> 00:24:06.903
I can't lose hours for extra lessons.

433
00:24:14.453 --> 00:24:15.787
[exhales]

434
00:24:16.371 --> 00:24:17.497
Okay. then.

435
00:24:18.707 --> 00:24:22.586
What if I pay you enough to make up
for any lost hours you may miss?

436
00:24:25.172 --> 00:24:26.631
[snorting chuckle]

437
00:24:27.716 --> 00:24:29.009
[chuckles]

438
00:24:30.343 --> 00:24:31.553
Why?

439
00:24:32.304 --> 00:24:33.221
[chuckles softly]

440
00:24:34.181 --> 00:24:35.056
Pay me for what?

441
00:24:36.683 --> 00:24:38.602
[both laugh]

442
00:24:39.102 --> 00:24:41.271
Christ. No. that's crazy.

443
00:24:41.354 --> 00:24:43.023
[rhythmic jazzy music playing]

444
00:24:46.151 --> 00:24:47.486
[breathes pensively]

445
00:24:47.986 --> 00:24:48.904
[clears throat]

446
00:24:50.197 --> 00:24:51.031
Lee Kang.

447
00:24:53.158 --> 00:24:54.159
[sighs]

448
00:24:54.242 --> 00:24:57.621
Now. I'm serious. Stop being silly.
and listen to me carefully.

449
00:24:58.497 --> 00:24:59.831
-[music continues]
-[grunts]

450
00:24:59.915 --> 00:25:02.167
[Mun-oh] <i>You'll never be Kim Se-yun.</i>

451
00:25:02.667 --> 00:25:06.463
<i>but you can write as much as you want</i>
<i>about your desire to become him.</i>

452
00:25:07.839 --> 00:25:09.758
<i>If you can digest that feeling.</i>

453
00:25:10.550 --> 00:25:12.010
<i>that's what writing is.</i>

454
00:25:12.093 --> 00:25:14.137
<i>That's the power of literature.</i>

455
00:25:16.515 --> 00:25:22.103
<i>I want to help you. so that what you write</i>
<i>doesn't end up just marks on a page.</i>

456
00:25:22.771 --> 00:25:24.439
<i>but becomes a story.</i>

457
00:25:26.775 --> 00:25:30.070
Because… talent is a rare thing.

458
00:25:30.862 --> 00:25:32.531
And I'd like to teach you.

459
00:25:33.281 --> 00:25:34.366
ALL RIGHT. PROFESSOR

460
00:25:34.449 --> 00:25:38.161
[Kang] <i>All right. Professor.</i>
<i>I'll quit one of my part-time jobs.</i>

461
00:25:38.245 --> 00:25:39.329
[jazzy music continues]

462
00:25:46.920 --> 00:25:50.549
ALL RIGHT. TEACHER
I'LL QUIT ONE OF MY PART-TIME JOBS

463
00:25:51.132 --> 00:25:53.134
[jaunty music playing]

464
00:26:09.651 --> 00:26:10.819
[contentedly] Hmm.

465
00:26:14.698 --> 00:26:15.740
Hmm.

466
00:26:23.415 --> 00:26:24.833
[Mun-oh rummaging]

467
00:26:28.962 --> 00:26:30.088
[music fades]

468
00:26:32.048 --> 00:26:33.842
-What is it?
-[chuckles]

469
00:26:34.467 --> 00:26:36.011
I just find it funny.

470
00:26:36.803 --> 00:26:40.056
Individual lessons?
I didn't think you'd actually do it.

471
00:26:41.683 --> 00:26:44.519
Anyway. you look happier
than I've seen you in a while.

472
00:26:44.603 --> 00:26:47.939
I thought you had an appointment.
I don't want you to be late.

473
00:26:48.023 --> 00:26:49.566
Better get going. hmm?

474
00:26:51.109 --> 00:26:54.195
I'm not sure I feel comfortable
about you doing the lessons here.

475
00:26:54.279 --> 00:26:57.407
Why at home?
Why not at school or a coffee shop?

476
00:26:58.199 --> 00:27:02.662
Because then people will see us.
I'd rather give it a few weeks first.

477
00:27:04.331 --> 00:27:08.168
And when you see Park and Seong-hui.
please. you can't tell them either. okay?

478
00:27:08.668 --> 00:27:10.128
-Say I had plans.
-Jeez. All right.

479
00:27:10.211 --> 00:27:13.131
Why do you always wanna
keep everything such a secret?

480
00:27:15.550 --> 00:27:17.344
See you later. Have a good lesson.

481
00:27:17.427 --> 00:27:18.428
[Mun-oh] Mm-hmm.

482
00:27:21.514 --> 00:27:23.516
[footsteps departing]

483
00:27:24.934 --> 00:27:26.728
-[tuts]
-[door opens in distance]

484
00:27:28.480 --> 00:27:29.439
[door closes]

485
00:27:35.153 --> 00:27:36.404
[books slide gently]

486
00:27:57.050 --> 00:27:58.802
[breathes deeply]

487
00:28:06.101 --> 00:28:09.229
[doorbell ringing]

488
00:28:10.313 --> 00:28:12.190
[breathes deeply]

489
00:28:15.610 --> 00:28:16.611
[door chimes]

490
00:28:17.362 --> 00:28:18.279
Hey.

491
00:28:19.823 --> 00:28:20.657
Come in.

492
00:28:20.740 --> 00:28:21.991
[dog barking in distance]

493
00:28:29.249 --> 00:28:30.125
[door chimes]

494
00:28:33.586 --> 00:28:34.504
Through here.

495
00:28:42.429 --> 00:28:43.555
What are you doing?

496
00:28:55.650 --> 00:28:58.319
Why do you look so down?
You came here to study.

497
00:28:58.820 --> 00:29:00.822
You haven't even said hello.

498
00:29:02.741 --> 00:29:04.033
I said hi.

499
00:29:04.909 --> 00:29:06.661
You didn't. Sit.

500
00:29:09.205 --> 00:29:10.498
Actually…

501
00:29:12.083 --> 00:29:13.084
[Kang sighs]

502
00:29:13.168 --> 00:29:16.379
Something happened.
and I… was gonna call and tell you.

503
00:29:16.880 --> 00:29:19.716
but I thought it would be better
to wait until I saw you.

504
00:29:21.593 --> 00:29:22.761
Mm. okay. Go ahead.

505
00:29:23.344 --> 00:29:24.471
[Kang sighs softly]

506
00:29:25.305 --> 00:29:26.848
I won't be able to do these lessons.

507
00:29:28.975 --> 00:29:30.852
-[Mun-oh huffs]
-So. um…

508
00:29:30.935 --> 00:29:32.604
I went over to Se-yun's house yesterday.

509
00:29:32.687 --> 00:29:35.190
and I… might not be able
to go back there again.

510
00:29:35.273 --> 00:29:37.275
Which would mean I can't write anymore.

511
00:29:37.776 --> 00:29:40.570
and. um. there'd be no point
in having these lessons.

512
00:29:41.112 --> 00:29:42.530
[hesitates] Okay.

513
00:29:43.031 --> 00:29:45.200
[splutters] Wha… what exactly happened?

514
00:29:45.283 --> 00:29:46.618
Wha… what's wrong?

515
00:29:52.832 --> 00:29:55.794
You know the computer coding club
Se-yun and I are in together?

516
00:29:55.877 --> 00:29:56.711
Yeah.

517
00:29:57.337 --> 00:29:59.964
Well. it's hosting a competition
in about two weeks.

518
00:30:00.465 --> 00:30:03.092
It's essentially the first round
for the national level.

519
00:30:03.593 --> 00:30:04.636
Uh…

520
00:30:06.387 --> 00:30:09.015
Se-yun and I decided
to pair up and enter it.

521
00:30:09.516 --> 00:30:12.685
So I went over to his house
to practice together. and then…

522
00:30:13.269 --> 00:30:14.145
And then?

523
00:30:15.480 --> 00:30:17.232
-Keep trying up to here.
-[Se-yun] Okay.

524
00:30:18.483 --> 00:30:19.901
I gotta go take a piss. okay?

525
00:30:19.984 --> 00:30:20.985
Sure. yeah.

526
00:30:21.069 --> 00:30:22.445
[keyboard clacking]

527
00:30:25.365 --> 00:30:26.282
Bracket…

528
00:30:26.950 --> 00:30:28.284
[toilet flushing]

529
00:30:41.381 --> 00:30:42.465
[light switch clacks]

530
00:30:44.342 --> 00:30:45.677
[gentle piano music playing]

531
00:30:51.975 --> 00:30:53.101
[birds chirping]

532
00:30:57.355 --> 00:30:59.691
[Kang] <i>I was only going to</i>
<i>use the bathroom.</i>

533
00:30:59.774 --> 00:31:01.734
<i>but then I got curious.</i>

534
00:31:03.486 --> 00:31:04.904
[soft. dreamy music playing]

535
00:31:21.045 --> 00:31:24.299
<i>I know… I shouldn't have done it.</i>

536
00:31:32.849 --> 00:31:34.350
[melodic piano music playing]

537
00:31:44.569 --> 00:31:46.905
[ethereal. lilting vocalizing]

538
00:32:25.234 --> 00:32:26.527
[dreamy music playing]

539
00:32:44.379 --> 00:32:46.172
-[sniffs softly]
-[footsteps approach]

540
00:32:46.255 --> 00:32:47.215
[music stops]

541
00:32:52.845 --> 00:32:54.180
[breathes hesitantly]

542
00:32:54.263 --> 00:32:55.640
I'm sorry. [chuckles awkwardly]

543
00:32:56.474 --> 00:32:58.309
I couldn't find the bathroom. so…

544
00:32:59.394 --> 00:33:00.311
Oh. [chuckles]

545
00:33:00.395 --> 00:33:03.648
Well. I thought that you were my Yun.

546
00:33:03.731 --> 00:33:05.566
There's actually a bathroom upstairs.

547
00:33:05.650 --> 00:33:08.236
And one by the front entrance for guests.

548
00:33:09.362 --> 00:33:11.197
Thanks for letting me know.

549
00:33:12.031 --> 00:33:13.616
I won't get lost again.

550
00:33:14.409 --> 00:33:15.410
[chuckles softly]

551
00:33:15.493 --> 00:33:17.412
[light. intriguing music playing]

552
00:33:19.080 --> 00:33:20.748
<i>Even though I was out of line.</i>

553
00:33:20.832 --> 00:33:22.875
<i>Se-yun's mom was kind to me.</i>

554
00:33:22.959 --> 00:33:25.670
<i>She didn't get mad or even seem upset.</i>

555
00:33:26.170 --> 00:33:28.589
<i>She didn't say anything</i>
<i>during dinner either.</i>

556
00:33:28.673 --> 00:33:30.508
-[mother] It's hot.
-[Se-yun] Mm-hmm.

557
00:33:30.591 --> 00:33:31.718
[music continues]

558
00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:35.722
Are you coming? What are you doing?

559
00:33:36.222 --> 00:33:37.890
Everybody's waiting for you.

560
00:33:38.474 --> 00:33:40.268
[man] Yeah. be right there.

561
00:33:48.109 --> 00:33:49.819
Mm… the new friend.

562
00:33:49.902 --> 00:33:52.822
I'm Se-yun's dad.
Your name is Lee Kang. right?

563
00:33:54.032 --> 00:33:55.867
-Hello.
-[father] Have a seat.

564
00:33:56.909 --> 00:33:58.119
[chuckles]

565
00:33:59.829 --> 00:34:02.373
I hear you're good with computers.

566
00:34:02.874 --> 00:34:05.168
You know. you're almost all
he talks about these days.

567
00:34:05.251 --> 00:34:06.210
[chuckles]

568
00:34:06.294 --> 00:34:08.463
-Seems like that.
-[father chuckles]

569
00:34:08.546 --> 00:34:10.715
He's had so many friends.
but he talks about you a lot.

570
00:34:10.798 --> 00:34:12.675
Oh. come on. Mom. not that much.

571
00:34:12.759 --> 00:34:16.554
But the only reason I'm in the competition
is 'cause Kang here is helping me out.

572
00:34:16.637 --> 00:34:17.472
[father] Hmm.

573
00:34:17.555 --> 00:34:19.974
He even impresses the seniors
with his skills.

574
00:34:20.892 --> 00:34:23.936
-Ah. you're exaggerating.
-[Se-yun] Exaggerating?

575
00:34:24.520 --> 00:34:26.689
Anyway. take good care of Se-yun.

576
00:34:27.190 --> 00:34:30.401
He dreams of becoming a programmer now.

577
00:34:30.485 --> 00:34:33.821
[chuckles] Had we known. we would've
sent him to engineering school. like you.

578
00:34:33.905 --> 00:34:36.074
-[chuckles] Okay. let's eat.
-[Se-yun chuckles]

579
00:34:36.157 --> 00:34:37.075
[father] Mm…

580
00:34:37.658 --> 00:34:39.660
-Mm-hmm!
-We'll say grace first.

581
00:34:39.744 --> 00:34:42.955
In the name of the Father. and of the Son.
and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

582
00:34:43.039 --> 00:34:44.624
Bless us. O Lord. and these Thy gifts.

583
00:34:44.707 --> 00:34:48.544
which we are about to receive
from Thy bounty. through Christ our Lord…

584
00:34:48.628 --> 00:34:52.757
[Kang] <i>But by the time I left that night.</i>
<i>I found out how she really felt about me.</i>

585
00:34:53.341 --> 00:34:57.428
[mother] I don't know.
He seems a bit sneaky or something.

586
00:34:58.137 --> 00:35:00.181
People have a certain vibe to them.

587
00:35:01.307 --> 00:35:03.142
I felt it the first time I met him.

588
00:35:03.226 --> 00:35:04.936
[tuts] I wish he'd stop coming over.

589
00:35:05.853 --> 00:35:07.355
[father] Mm-hmm? What is it?

590
00:35:07.438 --> 00:35:08.981
[soft. uneasy music playing]

591
00:35:09.816 --> 00:35:11.776
What's got you all worked up now?

592
00:35:13.861 --> 00:35:16.614
We shouldn't talk like this
about a friend of Se-yun's.

593
00:35:17.115 --> 00:35:19.325
All we can do is watch over him.

594
00:35:20.535 --> 00:35:23.871
[mother] Something happened today.
He was in our bedroom.

595
00:35:25.665 --> 00:35:26.624
I just… [sighs]

596
00:35:26.707 --> 00:35:27.875
I'm just saying.

597
00:35:27.959 --> 00:35:32.547
I'd rather our Yun be friends
with someone… more cheerful and friendly.

598
00:35:32.630 --> 00:35:34.549
[inhales sharply] Oh. jeez.

599
00:35:35.466 --> 00:35:38.094
I thought he was fine.
He looks like a smart kid.

600
00:35:38.928 --> 00:35:40.221
How about this?

601
00:35:40.304 --> 00:35:42.932
We leave it alone
until after the competition.

602
00:35:43.599 --> 00:35:45.768
Who knows? They might even win an award.

603
00:35:46.561 --> 00:35:49.021
Winning an award at a competition
like that will be good for him

604
00:35:49.105 --> 00:35:51.107
when he starts applying for jobs.

605
00:35:51.190 --> 00:35:53.526
[mother] That's been on my mind too.

606
00:35:54.527 --> 00:35:55.361
All right.

607
00:35:56.195 --> 00:35:58.197
If it means he'll be better off.

608
00:35:58.948 --> 00:36:00.616
let's wait and see what happens.

609
00:36:00.700 --> 00:36:01.534
[father] Yeah.

610
00:36:01.617 --> 00:36:03.953
-[uneasy music continues]
-[wine glasses clink]

611
00:36:04.704 --> 00:36:06.330
[Kang exhales deeply]

612
00:36:07.039 --> 00:36:07.999
[music ends]

613
00:36:09.041 --> 00:36:09.959
[chuckles softly]

614
00:36:13.671 --> 00:36:15.756
Well. what'd you do that for. huh?

615
00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:17.717
I know I shouldn't have done it.

616
00:36:19.719 --> 00:36:20.928
[sighs] All right.

617
00:36:21.429 --> 00:36:23.097
So what this means is

618
00:36:24.140 --> 00:36:25.933
you have to win in the competition.

619
00:36:26.017 --> 00:36:29.437
or whatever you call it.
so they'll keep letting you go over there?

620
00:36:29.520 --> 00:36:30.855
Hmm? Is that it?

621
00:36:30.938 --> 00:36:32.815
Yeah. That's how it is.

622
00:36:33.399 --> 00:36:34.609
So then. win it.

623
00:36:34.692 --> 00:36:36.861
I'm getting the impression
you're good at it.

624
00:36:36.944 --> 00:36:38.905
You have no idea. I'm better than Se-yun.

625
00:36:38.988 --> 00:36:41.657
But there's no chance
I could win the competition.

626
00:36:43.868 --> 00:36:45.453
[Mun-oh sighs deeply]

627
00:36:46.495 --> 00:36:47.747
Okay. but still.

628
00:36:48.247 --> 00:36:51.334
who says you have to go
into that house in order to write?

629
00:36:51.834 --> 00:36:52.710
[Kang sighs]

630
00:36:53.502 --> 00:36:54.712
Don't you understand?

631
00:36:54.795 --> 00:36:57.590
What do I write about?
I don't have anything else.

632
00:36:59.592 --> 00:37:00.551
You're right.

633
00:37:01.135 --> 00:37:03.346
Yep. that's true. [sighs]

634
00:37:03.429 --> 00:37:04.430
That's true.

635
00:37:05.014 --> 00:37:06.432
[inhales deeply]

636
00:37:06.515 --> 00:37:08.601
Oh. what do we do?

637
00:37:09.101 --> 00:37:13.022
We need to come up… with a good idea.

638
00:37:14.690 --> 00:37:17.652
There's one thing that might work. but…

639
00:37:19.445 --> 00:37:20.529
Well. what is it?

640
00:37:28.162 --> 00:37:29.664
[scoffs] Forget it.

641
00:37:30.498 --> 00:37:32.166
I don't think you'd do it.

642
00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:35.670
What are you talking about. huh?
What wouldn't I do? Tell me.

643
00:37:38.881 --> 00:37:40.007
[exhales hesitantly]

644
00:37:43.970 --> 00:37:45.054
The questions.

645
00:37:46.555 --> 00:37:47.848
The questions?

646
00:37:51.102 --> 00:37:52.270
What about them?

647
00:38:04.949 --> 00:38:05.866
[scoffs softly]

648
00:38:07.285 --> 00:38:08.411
You don't mean…

649
00:38:11.372 --> 00:38:13.207
You wouldn't ask me…

650
00:38:15.209 --> 00:38:16.544
to find out what…

651
00:38:18.546 --> 00:38:20.631
the questions are gonna be. right?

652
00:38:21.757 --> 00:38:24.051
I would never ask that.
but what else can we do?

653
00:38:29.265 --> 00:38:30.516
Are you crazy?

654
00:38:32.935 --> 00:38:34.353
Oh my God. You are.

655
00:38:38.691 --> 00:38:39.900
You punk!

656
00:38:41.319 --> 00:38:43.112
How dare you suggest that to your teacher?

657
00:38:43.195 --> 00:38:44.822
Who do you think you are?

658
00:38:45.448 --> 00:38:47.700
How could you ask me to cheat for you?

659
00:38:49.535 --> 00:38:51.287
[gasping]

660
00:38:52.121 --> 00:38:53.581
Hey. get out!

661
00:38:54.623 --> 00:38:55.875
Get outta here!

662
00:38:55.958 --> 00:38:57.835
I'm not giving you lessons anymore.

663
00:38:58.336 --> 00:39:00.421
You know. you're a real piece of work.

664
00:39:02.340 --> 00:39:03.591
Now. get out!

665
00:39:07.720 --> 00:39:09.138
Then it can't be helped.

666
00:39:09.221 --> 00:39:10.222
[inhales deeply]

667
00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:13.642
Why don't we pretend
this whole thing never happened?

668
00:39:19.940 --> 00:39:21.317
[footsteps departing]

669
00:39:22.234 --> 00:39:23.736
What are you trying to do?

670
00:39:24.236 --> 00:39:25.237
[scoffs incredulously]

671
00:39:25.321 --> 00:39:28.324
-You're some kind of asshole? Huh?
-[door opens. closes]

672
00:39:28.407 --> 00:39:30.034
-[door chimes]
-[glasses clatter]

673
00:39:30.117 --> 00:39:31.577
[tense music playing]

674
00:39:40.378 --> 00:39:42.505
Why didn't you hand in
your assignment this week?

675
00:39:43.047 --> 00:39:44.840
I had nothing to write about.

676
00:39:50.471 --> 00:39:51.639
[car window whirs]

677
00:39:53.307 --> 00:39:54.183
Hey. Lee Kang!

678
00:39:54.266 --> 00:39:55.309
[whimsical music playing]

679
00:39:55.393 --> 00:39:57.061
Aren't you gonna hand anything in?

680
00:39:57.561 --> 00:39:59.313
If you don't. you won't get a grade!

681
00:40:02.066 --> 00:40:03.150
Hey.

682
00:40:04.318 --> 00:40:05.277
Hey!

683
00:40:05.361 --> 00:40:06.737
ELECTRONIC ENGINEERING
LEE KANG

684
00:40:07.863 --> 00:40:09.240
[whimsical music continues]

685
00:40:18.791 --> 00:40:20.167
[whimsical music continues]

686
00:40:23.712 --> 00:40:27.716
GUEST LECTURE WITH AUTHOR KIM SU-HUN

687
00:40:29.593 --> 00:40:30.970
AUTHOR OF EYES OF THE HOUSE

688
00:40:43.858 --> 00:40:44.900
[handbrake clacks]

689
00:40:44.984 --> 00:40:46.193
[music fades]

690
00:40:46.277 --> 00:40:47.528
-[engine stops]
-[sighs]

691
00:40:49.447 --> 00:40:51.198
[students chattering indistinctly]

692
00:40:56.370 --> 00:40:57.246
[exhales]

693
00:40:59.039 --> 00:41:00.624
[cell phone vibrates]

694
00:41:01.542 --> 00:41:03.252
[vibrating continues]

695
00:41:08.841 --> 00:41:10.134
Hello. Mr. Park.

696
00:41:10.217 --> 00:41:13.012
[Mr. Park] <i>Hey. Mun-oh. I mean… Mr. Heo.</i>

697
00:41:13.095 --> 00:41:14.847
[chuckles] <i>Uh. where are you?</i>

698
00:41:15.347 --> 00:41:16.265
Oh. uh…

699
00:41:16.348 --> 00:41:18.893
<i>Mr. Kim is already here</i>
<i>and waiting for you.</i>

700
00:41:19.393 --> 00:41:22.104
<i>You two should have a cup of coffee</i>
<i>and chat before the lecture.</i>

701
00:41:22.188 --> 00:41:24.356
Oh. really? Uh… he's waiting?

702
00:41:24.440 --> 00:41:26.609
I'm on my way now. I just parked.

703
00:41:27.109 --> 00:41:30.154
Ten minutes. I think I'll be there
in about ten minutes.

704
00:41:30.237 --> 00:41:34.783
Tell him to. uh… have a cup of tea
and wait a little longer. okay? Yeah.

705
00:41:35.284 --> 00:41:37.578
Sorry about that. Be right there. Yeah.

706
00:41:38.579 --> 00:41:39.872
Sure. All right. Yeah.

707
00:41:41.832 --> 00:41:42.791
[cell phone beeps]

708
00:41:43.834 --> 00:41:44.877
[sighs]

709
00:41:50.508 --> 00:41:51.509
[whimsical music playing]

710
00:41:52.134 --> 00:41:53.928
Ah! It's been a while.

711
00:41:54.762 --> 00:41:57.806
-It really has. hasn't it? Yeah.
-It sure has. Too many years.

712
00:41:57.890 --> 00:42:00.059
Hey. when was the last time
we saw each other?

713
00:42:00.142 --> 00:42:01.852
I can't remember anything these days.

714
00:42:01.936 --> 00:42:04.813
Ah… Let's see. um… When was it?

715
00:42:04.897 --> 00:42:06.524
Sorry. No. I'm not sure either.

716
00:42:06.607 --> 00:42:08.150
-[chuckles]
-[Mr. Park chuckles]

717
00:42:08.234 --> 00:42:11.070
This is great.
to see a reunion of old friends.

718
00:42:11.153 --> 00:42:14.281
I've never seen Mr. Heo
with such a big smile on his face.

719
00:42:14.365 --> 00:42:16.534
-Oh. is that right?
-[Mr. Park laughs]

720
00:42:17.243 --> 00:42:20.788
Yeah. It's true. It feels great.

721
00:42:20.871 --> 00:42:23.958
-[chuckling]
-You haven't changed a bit. [chuckles]

722
00:42:24.041 --> 00:42:28.462
Through seven full-length novels
and four short story collections.

723
00:42:28.546 --> 00:42:31.006
Mr. Kim… um…

724
00:42:31.090 --> 00:42:34.635
you've plumbed the rich depths
of the human psyche.

725
00:42:34.718 --> 00:42:37.555
But in your latest novel.
<i>Eyes of the House</i>.

726
00:42:37.638 --> 00:42:40.057
you attempted something very different.

727
00:42:40.140 --> 00:42:42.935
You decided to include
aspects of the mystery genre.

728
00:42:43.018 --> 00:42:46.939
Yes. that's right.
I borrowed from mystery novels.

729
00:42:47.481 --> 00:42:51.443
But while your standard mystery
focuses on solving the murder.

730
00:42:51.527 --> 00:42:54.113
I was interested
in something a bit different.

731
00:42:54.863 --> 00:42:57.449
I took all the scenes.
including those of the murder.

732
00:42:57.533 --> 00:42:59.368
tore them into pieces.
and scrambled them up.

733
00:42:59.451 --> 00:43:03.122
so no one could be sure
what the real sequence was.

734
00:43:04.290 --> 00:43:08.627
What was important wasn't the revelation
of the mystery for the reader.

735
00:43:08.711 --> 00:43:10.796
nor was it even
the conclusion of the case.

736
00:43:10.879 --> 00:43:14.133
Instead. it was the fascinating ways
the characters relate to one another

737
00:43:14.216 --> 00:43:15.175
that I focused on.

738
00:43:17.928 --> 00:43:19.054
You got that. right?

739
00:43:20.347 --> 00:43:21.432
Well. I got it.

740
00:43:21.515 --> 00:43:23.517
-[audience laughs]
-[Mun-oh chuckles]

741
00:43:23.601 --> 00:43:25.102
Yes. it's truly…

742
00:43:25.185 --> 00:43:26.520
Well. it's remarkable.

743
00:43:26.604 --> 00:43:28.439
That's the reason so many

744
00:43:28.939 --> 00:43:32.776
have called this book "very exciting."
"truly unexpected." and "refreshing."

745
00:43:33.569 --> 00:43:34.945
However… [sighs]

746
00:43:35.029 --> 00:43:36.280
Yeah. Hmm.

747
00:43:37.906 --> 00:43:40.242
However… hmm…

748
00:43:40.326 --> 00:43:41.660
there are those…

749
00:43:42.453 --> 00:43:45.080
mm… hmm… mm…

750
00:43:45.164 --> 00:43:46.457
"There are those…"?

751
00:43:47.791 --> 00:43:49.710
Mm. let's just say. um.

752
00:43:49.793 --> 00:43:52.421
there are those who might say…

753
00:43:53.964 --> 00:43:56.258
Uh. and I'm sorry… [chuckles]

754
00:43:56.342 --> 00:43:58.677
…if it's uncomfortable for you to hear.

755
00:43:59.178 --> 00:44:02.556
But we're all here
for free discussion. aren't we?

756
00:44:02.640 --> 00:44:04.058
So I'll say it. Hmm?

757
00:44:06.518 --> 00:44:09.938
With this book. Kim Su-hun is now
a writer who accommodates the masses.

758
00:44:10.022 --> 00:44:11.732
Well. that is… [chuckles]

759
00:44:11.815 --> 00:44:16.236
That's an example of the sort
of critical opinions that are out there.

760
00:44:16.320 --> 00:44:17.363
[chuckles awkwardly]

761
00:44:18.280 --> 00:44:21.909
To be clear.
it. it. it's not one I agree with.

762
00:44:21.992 --> 00:44:24.620
The fact is. in advance of this interview.

763
00:44:24.703 --> 00:44:27.873
I received a few questions
from students for you.

764
00:44:27.956 --> 00:44:30.751
Mm. This was one of the questions.

765
00:44:30.834 --> 00:44:31.794
Uh…

766
00:44:31.877 --> 00:44:33.504
Mm. it's right here. Um…

767
00:44:33.587 --> 00:44:35.339
All right. uh…

768
00:44:36.215 --> 00:44:38.342
Let me see. [sighs]

769
00:44:39.301 --> 00:44:40.219
Where is it?

770
00:44:40.302 --> 00:44:41.720
Uh… Ah. here it is.

771
00:44:42.221 --> 00:44:43.597
Ah. so this…

772
00:44:44.640 --> 00:44:47.559
This is the one I was thinking of. Uh…

773
00:44:48.227 --> 00:44:53.816
"Mr. Kim Su-hun. you've long established
a reputation in literary fiction.

774
00:44:53.899 --> 00:44:56.485
and so I had great respect for you."

775
00:44:56.568 --> 00:44:58.904
"I was a huge fan of yours."

776
00:44:59.613 --> 00:45:04.910
"But I was very disappointed
to see you come out with a mystery novel."

777
00:45:05.411 --> 00:45:09.206
"Is it because you don't have
any stories left of your own.

778
00:45:09.707 --> 00:45:13.711
so all you could do
was accommodate the masses?"

779
00:45:14.878 --> 00:45:17.297
That's a tough one. [chuckles]

780
00:45:17.381 --> 00:45:19.842
"If you don't have anything left to say.

781
00:45:20.968 --> 00:45:23.053
um. shouldn't you

782
00:45:23.637 --> 00:45:28.100
face the truth
and quit writing altogether?"

783
00:45:28.934 --> 00:45:30.644
More or less. [chuckles awkwardly]

784
00:45:31.437 --> 00:45:33.230
First. which student asked this?

785
00:45:35.023 --> 00:45:37.693
[audience murmuring indistinctly]

786
00:45:41.822 --> 00:45:44.032
This isn't your question. is it. Mr. Heo?

787
00:45:44.658 --> 00:45:46.618
What? Uh. no. No. it's…

788
00:45:46.702 --> 00:45:49.079
[laughs] I'm just kidding.

789
00:45:49.830 --> 00:45:52.541
Whoever you are. I want to thank you
for bringing up this point.

790
00:45:52.624 --> 00:45:54.001
You sound like a fan of my work.

791
00:45:54.626 --> 00:45:57.296
Not only that. but you seem to be
interested in me as well.

792
00:45:57.379 --> 00:46:02.009
To answer your question. yes.
I am accommodating. That's right.

793
00:46:03.761 --> 00:46:06.638
"Accommodate" actually has a few meanings.

794
00:46:06.722 --> 00:46:10.809
"To ingratiate oneself for personal gain."

795
00:46:11.310 --> 00:46:14.938
We typically think of
this use of the word. but it also means

796
00:46:15.898 --> 00:46:17.357
"to make space for."

797
00:46:18.358 --> 00:46:20.694
In that sense. accommodation is invaluable

798
00:46:21.195 --> 00:46:22.946
in the world of literature.

799
00:46:23.447 --> 00:46:25.616
What do we need right now

800
00:46:25.699 --> 00:46:30.037
but authors who are willing
to make space with their work?

801
00:46:31.038 --> 00:46:34.708
Always. what truly matters
is not "what." but "how."

802
00:46:35.209 --> 00:46:38.337
A flexible and multifaceted perspective
is crucial.

803
00:46:38.921 --> 00:46:41.632
If you insist on sticking
to the worldview you're familiar with.

804
00:46:41.715 --> 00:46:43.759
your creativity will soon wither.

805
00:46:44.551 --> 00:46:45.928
That is why I will continue

806
00:46:46.011 --> 00:46:48.514
to tell new stories.
and experiment with new forms.

807
00:46:48.597 --> 00:46:50.057
and strive to become better

808
00:46:50.140 --> 00:46:52.059
at accommodating the masses.

809
00:46:52.142 --> 00:46:53.977
[audience applauds]

810
00:46:54.061 --> 00:46:56.104
[poignant piano music playing]

811
00:47:01.026 --> 00:47:02.528
[applause fades]

812
00:47:04.613 --> 00:47:07.533
[Mr. Park] Wow. The atmosphere
was <i>so </i>great today. wasn't it?

813
00:47:07.616 --> 00:47:09.618
-They were amazed. They were…
-[men chuckle]

814
00:47:09.701 --> 00:47:11.161
-It was really good.
-Mr. Kim.

815
00:47:11.245 --> 00:47:12.079
-Thanks.
-Uh…

816
00:47:12.162 --> 00:47:14.373
You know. of all the events
we've had so far.

817
00:47:14.456 --> 00:47:16.250
today's had the highest attendance.

818
00:47:16.333 --> 00:47:18.335
I've never seen the dean so excited.

819
00:47:18.418 --> 00:47:19.419
-[chuckles]
-Oh!

820
00:47:19.503 --> 00:47:21.797
It was all thanks to you.
but you made me look good.

821
00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:24.800
[Su-hun] Oh no. it's not thanks to me.
It's thanks to you. Mr. Park.

822
00:47:24.883 --> 00:47:26.969
And Mr. Heo too.
who hosted the conversation.

823
00:47:27.052 --> 00:47:27.886
[chuckles]

824
00:47:27.970 --> 00:47:29.137
But more than anything.

825
00:47:29.221 --> 00:47:31.348
the students who paid
such close attention.

826
00:47:31.431 --> 00:47:33.559
I got so excited
that I talked a bit too much.

827
00:47:33.642 --> 00:47:34.643
Ah. well. thank you.

828
00:47:34.726 --> 00:47:36.895
[woman 1] The students were
really into it today.

829
00:47:36.979 --> 00:47:38.856
If only they acted like that
at my lectures.

830
00:47:38.939 --> 00:47:40.983
-Yeah.
-[Mr. Park] You just have to do better.

831
00:47:41.066 --> 00:47:43.068
Cheers to you. It's been an honor.

832
00:47:43.151 --> 00:47:45.362
-[Su-hun] Cheers. Great to meet you.
-[Mr. Park] An honor.

833
00:47:45.445 --> 00:47:46.572
-Cheers.
-[Su-hun] Thank you.

834
00:47:46.655 --> 00:47:47.990
-[woman 1] You too.
-[Mun-oh] Hmm.

835
00:47:49.116 --> 00:47:50.576
[Su-hun chuckles softly]

836
00:47:53.829 --> 00:47:56.790
Hey there. Mr. Heo.
why have you been so quiet tonight?

837
00:47:57.749 --> 00:47:58.876
Oh. no reason.

838
00:47:58.959 --> 00:48:01.587
Just enjoying the company
and conversation.

839
00:48:01.670 --> 00:48:03.547
Oh yeah. You two are friends. right?

840
00:48:03.630 --> 00:48:05.048
Yes. from university.

841
00:48:05.132 --> 00:48:06.758
-[group] Oh!
-[Mr. Park chuckles]

842
00:48:07.259 --> 00:48:08.552
Is teaching enjoyable?

843
00:48:08.635 --> 00:48:10.679
[chuckles]

844
00:48:10.762 --> 00:48:12.973
-Enjoyable? Are you kidding?
-[group chuckles]

845
00:48:13.056 --> 00:48:15.183
-[woman 1 knowingly] Mm!
-[man 1] Oh. Mr. Kim.

846
00:48:15.267 --> 00:48:18.478
Your daughter's pen name
is Lee I-pil. right?

847
00:48:18.979 --> 00:48:22.316
Didn't she make her debut
with <i>Seventeen Green Wings </i>last year?

848
00:48:22.399 --> 00:48:24.234
-[woman 2] Wow! Really? Wait.
-[Su-hun] She did.

849
00:48:24.318 --> 00:48:26.987
[woman 2] That's the writer
who won the Literary Debut Award.

850
00:48:27.070 --> 00:48:30.824
-She's your daughter? Wow!
-[Mr. Park] Yeah. glad to hear about that.

851
00:48:30.908 --> 00:48:34.036
Oh. jeez. huh?
There are no more secrets in this world.

852
00:48:34.119 --> 00:48:37.706
Guess who thought of her pen name
so people wouldn't know who she is.

853
00:48:37.789 --> 00:48:39.708
-That's great!
-Everyone knows now. I guess.

854
00:48:39.791 --> 00:48:42.044
[man 1] It just means
talent runs in the family.

855
00:48:42.127 --> 00:48:44.588
-Oh. you must be so proud. I envy you.
-[sighs deeply]

856
00:48:45.088 --> 00:48:47.424
[woman 2] How did you manage
to raise such an amazing kid.

857
00:48:47.507 --> 00:48:48.884
on top of everything else?

858
00:48:48.967 --> 00:48:51.720
-You have it all. You do.
-[man 2] I envy you too.

859
00:48:52.220 --> 00:48:55.265
My kid's still trying to figure out
what he wants to do with himself.

860
00:48:55.349 --> 00:48:57.809
-[group laughing]
-[acoustic guitar music playing]

861
00:49:00.062 --> 00:49:01.188
[grunts wearily]

862
00:49:04.983 --> 00:49:06.193
[music continues]

863
00:49:47.401 --> 00:49:48.652
-[music ends]
-Professor.

864
00:49:49.736 --> 00:49:50.946
What are you…

865
00:49:51.571 --> 00:49:53.073
[distant siren wailing]

866
00:49:54.950 --> 00:49:55.867
You work here?

867
00:49:56.618 --> 00:49:57.452
Yeah.

868
00:49:59.037 --> 00:50:00.998
You're having dinner here. I guess?

869
00:50:01.790 --> 00:50:02.791
[Mun-oh] Mm.

870
00:50:04.251 --> 00:50:06.503
So what was that
you were busy writing there?

871
00:50:08.505 --> 00:50:09.423
Oh.

872
00:50:11.550 --> 00:50:12.884
This is just… [chuckles]

873
00:50:13.468 --> 00:50:16.430
Well. I'm just curious.
You don't turn anything in. so…

874
00:50:18.140 --> 00:50:19.016
Well.

875
00:50:20.225 --> 00:50:21.601
the truth is. I…

876
00:50:22.185 --> 00:50:23.186
[inhales deeply]

877
00:50:23.895 --> 00:50:28.233
I was thinking of submitting something
to a contest. Literary Debut Award.

878
00:50:29.151 --> 00:50:32.320
I heard their first prize money
is pretty big. so why not. right?

879
00:50:32.404 --> 00:50:34.322
Wait. what? An award?

880
00:50:35.240 --> 00:50:36.825
I thought about what you said.

881
00:50:38.285 --> 00:50:39.411
That I have talent.

882
00:50:41.705 --> 00:50:45.375
<i>I just… haven't found</i>
<i>a story I want to write yet.</i>

883
00:50:50.047 --> 00:50:50.964
[gulps]

884
00:50:52.382 --> 00:50:54.217
[grunts. sighs]

885
00:50:55.510 --> 00:50:57.012
[relieved sigh]

886
00:50:58.221 --> 00:50:59.848
[exhales deeply]

887
00:51:02.267 --> 00:51:06.188
[sighs] Literary Debut Award.

888
00:51:07.230 --> 00:51:08.899
[chuckles]

889
00:51:09.983 --> 00:51:11.526
Little shit.

890
00:51:12.444 --> 00:51:13.403
[gulps]

891
00:51:15.822 --> 00:51:17.991
The audacity.

892
00:51:19.826 --> 00:51:20.994
[sighs]

893
00:51:21.078 --> 00:51:23.789
-[crowd applauding]
-[triumphant music playing]

894
00:51:25.791 --> 00:51:26.958
{\an8}LITERARY DEBUT AWARD
LEE KANG

895
00:51:27.042 --> 00:51:29.086
Uh… Thank you.

896
00:51:29.586 --> 00:51:30.879
Thank you very much.

897
00:51:32.422 --> 00:51:33.381
[applause subsides]

898
00:51:33.465 --> 00:51:36.259
Someone else actually deserves this award.

899
00:51:36.343 --> 00:51:37.302
[music abates]

900
00:51:37.385 --> 00:51:40.430
The one who told me. "You have talent."

901
00:51:40.972 --> 00:51:43.850
The one who opened my eyes
to what was possible.

902
00:51:44.351 --> 00:51:45.852
who taught me everything.

903
00:51:46.394 --> 00:51:49.648
From what real writing is
to what it means to really live.

904
00:51:49.731 --> 00:51:51.149
[rousing jazz playing]

905
00:51:53.276 --> 00:51:54.861
Mr. Heo Mun-oh.

906
00:51:57.697 --> 00:51:59.616
I'll always be grateful to you.

907
00:52:01.034 --> 00:52:02.202
[crowd applauds]

908
00:52:04.746 --> 00:52:05.664
[music builds]

909
00:52:06.248 --> 00:52:08.083
[saxophone playing solo]

910
00:52:18.093 --> 00:52:19.177
[music peaks]

911
00:52:19.261 --> 00:52:20.303
[music subsides]

912
00:52:20.971 --> 00:52:23.557
[rippling piano notes descending]

913
00:52:26.059 --> 00:52:27.853
[distant car honks]

914
00:52:30.689 --> 00:52:31.731
[music fades]

915
00:52:31.815 --> 00:52:33.275
[breathing heavily]

916
00:52:36.111 --> 00:52:37.112
[chuckles softly]

917
00:52:57.257 --> 00:52:58.133
[smacks lips]

918
00:52:58.842 --> 00:52:59.843
[sighs]

919
00:53:00.844 --> 00:53:01.761
Look.

920
00:53:03.471 --> 00:53:07.350
The Literary Debut Award contest
isn't some kind of game. you know.

921
00:53:09.019 --> 00:53:12.063
You wouldn't stand a chance
with your current writing skills.

922
00:53:13.398 --> 00:53:14.232
[tuts]

923
00:53:16.026 --> 00:53:17.527
[sighs wearily]

924
00:53:17.611 --> 00:53:18.862
[groans]

925
00:53:21.656 --> 00:53:22.741
[inhales deeply]

926
00:53:22.824 --> 00:53:24.326
[sighs. scoffs]

927
00:53:24.910 --> 00:53:25.827
Listen.

928
00:53:26.912 --> 00:53:27.829
[blows]

929
00:53:28.580 --> 00:53:29.623
Hypothetically…

930
00:53:30.123 --> 00:53:34.753
[scoffs] …if you got the questions
ahead of time for the coding competition…

931
00:53:36.796 --> 00:53:38.048
[hesitates]

932
00:53:38.715 --> 00:53:42.135
…would it make you…
start taking writing seriously?

933
00:53:44.137 --> 00:53:46.556
Would you take individual lessons from me?

934
00:53:55.482 --> 00:53:56.566
[sighs]

935
00:53:58.860 --> 00:54:01.613
Tell me. Tell me. what do I need to do?

936
00:54:01.696 --> 00:54:03.323
Come on. What's the plan?

937
00:54:03.406 --> 00:54:04.241
[tuts]

938
00:54:04.741 --> 00:54:05.617
[huffs]

939
00:54:07.786 --> 00:54:09.037
[Mun-oh sighs softly]

940
00:54:15.168 --> 00:54:16.836
Are you sure you're okay with this?

941
00:54:16.920 --> 00:54:18.213
[suspenseful music playing]

942
00:54:18.296 --> 00:54:21.466
<i>It'll be easy.</i>
<i>You just need to do as I say.</i>

943
00:54:21.549 --> 00:54:23.843
[Mun-oh sighs] <i>What exactly</i>
<i>do I need to do?</i>

944
00:54:23.927 --> 00:54:26.263
[Kang] <i>First. go to</i>
<i>Professor Park's office.</i>

945
00:54:26.763 --> 00:54:28.014
[Mun-oh] <i>Professor Park?</i>

946
00:54:28.807 --> 00:54:30.684
-<i>From the College of Engineering?</i>
-[Kang] <i>Yes.</i>

947
00:54:30.767 --> 00:54:33.270
<i>He's the head of the committee</i>
<i>for the coding competition.</i>

948
00:54:34.145 --> 00:54:37.732
[Mun-oh] <i>Oh. that guy.</i>
<i>He's got a finger in every pie.</i>

949
00:54:38.275 --> 00:54:41.319
<i>W… wait. Did you know that I know him?</i>

950
00:54:42.237 --> 00:54:44.531
[Kang] <i>Of course I know that.</i>
<i>That's why this'll work.</i>

951
00:54:44.614 --> 00:54:46.449
<i>What? I've seen you two talking.</i>

952
00:54:46.950 --> 00:54:49.244
-[boy] Enjoy your meal.
-Ah. yeah. Thank you.

953
00:54:49.995 --> 00:54:51.913
-[woman] Here you go. Enjoy.
-Thank you very much.

954
00:54:52.872 --> 00:54:54.082
[music continues]

955
00:54:55.292 --> 00:54:57.919
-[boy] Hello. sir.
-[Mr. Park] Oh. Mm. [chuckles]

956
00:54:58.420 --> 00:54:59.629
[spoon scrapes]

957
00:55:01.131 --> 00:55:02.632
-[music ends]
-Mr. Park.

958
00:55:02.716 --> 00:55:04.217
Oh. Mun-oh!

959
00:55:04.301 --> 00:55:05.844
-[cutlery clatters]
-Come join me.

960
00:55:05.927 --> 00:55:07.971
-Having a late lunch?
-Yeah. you too…

961
00:55:08.054 --> 00:55:10.515
[Mun-oh] <i>All right.</i>
<i>so I go to Mr. Park's office.</i>

962
00:55:10.598 --> 00:55:12.267
<i>What do I do once I'm there?</i>

963
00:55:12.350 --> 00:55:13.768
[Kang] <i>The competition is tomorrow.</i>

964
00:55:13.852 --> 00:55:16.438
<i>so the questions will be</i>
<i>on Professor Park's computer.</i>

965
00:55:16.521 --> 00:55:19.899
<i>All you need to do is copy them</i>
<i>onto a USB drive. Simple. right?</i>

966
00:55:19.983 --> 00:55:21.443
[Mun-oh] <i>No. it's not simple!</i>

967
00:55:21.526 --> 00:55:23.320
<i>How am I supposed</i>
<i>to get into his computer?</i>

968
00:55:23.820 --> 00:55:25.488
<i>I don't know his password!</i>

969
00:55:25.572 --> 00:55:27.324
[Kang] <i>I know. I thought of that.</i>

970
00:55:27.407 --> 00:55:29.993
<i>Professor Park is going to</i>
<i>unlock it himself.</i>

971
00:55:33.496 --> 00:55:35.165
-[Mr. Park] Mm.
-Mr. Park.

972
00:55:35.248 --> 00:55:36.207
[Mr. Park] Hmm?

973
00:55:36.708 --> 00:55:40.170
I. um… would like to ask you a favor.

974
00:55:40.837 --> 00:55:43.340
Wow. You're asking me to do you a favor?

975
00:55:43.423 --> 00:55:44.632
[both chuckle]

976
00:55:44.716 --> 00:55:47.469
-Sure. go ahead.
-Uh. I just thought. um…

977
00:55:47.552 --> 00:55:52.223
I thought I'd make a little change
in my… my attendance system.

978
00:55:52.307 --> 00:55:53.391
-Really?
-Yeah.

979
00:55:53.475 --> 00:55:56.061
You were saying there was an easier way?

980
00:55:56.144 --> 00:55:58.897
Wow. I have to say.
this is music to my ears.

981
00:55:58.980 --> 00:56:00.982
Yeah. it's about time you changed it.

982
00:56:01.066 --> 00:56:02.484
[chuckles] Hey. how's this?

983
00:56:02.567 --> 00:56:04.861
I can come by your office
and install it for you.

984
00:56:04.944 --> 00:56:06.696
No. not at my office. Uh…

985
00:56:07.238 --> 00:56:09.699
I'd rather go to your office.

986
00:56:10.200 --> 00:56:15.205
Um… because I wanted to see
how it works. just to be sure.

987
00:56:15.789 --> 00:56:17.749
Uh-huh. Yeah?

988
00:56:17.832 --> 00:56:22.128
I'm. uh… I don't really have time today.
But you can come by my office tomorrow.

989
00:56:22.212 --> 00:56:23.213
-That works.
-Tomorrow?

990
00:56:23.713 --> 00:56:26.174
It won't work.
Tomorrow's the contest. Do it today.

991
00:56:26.257 --> 00:56:27.550
[tense music playing]

992
00:56:27.634 --> 00:56:29.886
Uh… That's not. uh… [chuckles]

993
00:56:29.969 --> 00:56:32.472
-Tomorrow's not good. I'm a bit busy.
-Mm-hmm?

994
00:56:33.264 --> 00:56:35.934
Couldn't we today?
It won't take long. will it?

995
00:56:36.017 --> 00:56:38.853
-Today? Right now?
-Sure. Just a few minutes.

996
00:56:39.437 --> 00:56:41.398
Okay. well.
I have a little time right now.

997
00:56:41.481 --> 00:56:44.150
-I'll just finish up.
-Great. Okay. Let's get going.

998
00:56:44.234 --> 00:56:45.151
[Mr. Park] Hmm?

999
00:56:45.235 --> 00:56:46.945
-Let's strike while the iron's hot.
-<i>Now </i>now?

1000
00:56:47.028 --> 00:56:49.572
Oh yeah. just for a bit.
Anyway. the food is… terrible.

1001
